================================
=== OJS TinyMCE Editor Plugin
=== Author: MJ Suhonos <mj@robotninja.com>
================================

About
-----
This plugin for OJS 2 converts all textareas to WYSIWYG XHTML editors using the TinyMCE cross-browser Javascript editor (http://tinymce.moxiecode.com/).  This allows authors, journal editors, etc. to enter valid XHTML into the various forms for more control over the appearance of their content.

License
-------
This plugin is licensed under the GNU General Public License v2. See the file COPYING for the complete terms of this license.

System Requirements
-------------------
The plugin requires the TinyMCE editor.  The latest release (2.0.6.1 as of this writing) can be downloaded at: http://tinymce.moxiecode.com/download.php

Installation
------------
To install the plugin:
 - download and extract the TinyMCE editor into lib/tinymce
 - as Journal Manager, go into the "System Plugins" page and enable the TinyMCE
   plugin.

Textareas/forms should now be enabled with the TinyMCE editor.

Localization
------------
TinyMCE language packs are available on the TinyMCE website at: http://tinymce.moxiecode.com/language.php

